,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',3,'/sites/m12','61ac89e104d8c6d5c0c9601c04315320','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','d563784a30f0e3761c5acfb8d0ac21a1',NULL),('9e4f5779-53d0-2ca9-7d75-16060940779a','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/main/node5389f82412566','5709f000-ead0-c557-e3f7-64d69421c923',1800,'a:4:{s:13:\"customTagName\";s:3:\"div\";s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"<h2>Summary</h2>\";s:9:\"classHide\";b:0;s:13:\"classClearfix\";b:0;}','TYPO3.Neos.NodeTypes:Headline',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',2,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/main','be8e3a3b189b018307aecc38a014e1d3','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','af55dff3a021a46d7b34772bf1d97f4f',NULL),('9ebc44f3-1854-ae5c-b0ee-2ee325508f33','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/main/node5389f4641324e','7cf01d8c-c881-906d-5595-2d26a83e5989',200,'a:4:{s:13:\"customTagName\";s:3:\"div\";s:4:\"text\";s:1362:\"<table><tbody><tr><td>TYPO3 CMS</td><td>Drupal</td><td>source</td></tr><tr><td>365k / 0.2%</td><td>707k / 0.4%</td><td><a href=\"http://builtwith.com/\">builtWith.com</a> (Total)</td></tr><tr><td>19k / 1%</td><td>46k / 2.4%</td><td><a href=\"http://builtwith.com/\">builtWith.com</a> (Top Sites)</td></tr><tr><td>4 / &lt;0.1%</td><td>387 / 3.9%</td><td>Quantcast Top 10k</td></tr></tbody></table><p> As you can see, TYPO3 has roughly 50% of what Drupal acquired so far, when it comes to totals. And this is fine - we do not compete here with Wordpress (12m 6.3%) or Joomla (2.7m 1.4%). It’s like with Jaguar cars: they are never going to beat Opel/Vauxhall quantitatively because they aim for something different. What worries me is that TYPO3 has such a small presence in top 10k websites - which in bystander\'s mind might rise a question ‘Is TYPO3 really that Jaguar’? I believe the one to blame for that achievement is <a href=\"http://www.acquia.com/\">Acquia</a> - Private Equity backed (<a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/acquia\">M</a>) company behind Drupal, co-founded by its creator, which does great marketing for it, supports enterprise clients who use Drupal, offers dedicated hosting, consultation, software, processes and so on. I was using some of these products and they’re truly impressive. TYPO3 doesn’t have such a back up.</p>\";s:9:\"classHide\";b:0;s:13:\"classClearfix\";b:0;}','TYPO3.Neos.NodeTypes:Text',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',2,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/main','ac0704381df1d3fb62cef840a7937c9f','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','af55dff3a021a46d7b34772bf1d97f4f',NULL),('a1cb52c9-ff9f-e371-767c-70beaf0a1d4b','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/main/node53712f7134e24/col1/column/node53712f478e475/col4/column/node5372893ba9ac6/content/node535ebc731aced','a6da7a54-6c13-f83c-f2fa-735bc489af31',300,'a:31:{s:5:\"label\";s:13:\"Sys-OP Hacker\";s:9:\"classHide\";b:0;s:13:\"classClearfix\";b:0;s:15:\"magellanSupport\";b:0;s:12:\"renderAnchor\";b:0;s:17:\"dropdownHoverable\";b:0;s:10:\"classFloat\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"classTextAlign\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"classRadiusAndRounded\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"classShowByScreenSize\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"classHideByScreenSize\";s:0:\"\";s:25:\"classOrientationDetection\";s:0:\"\";s:19:\"classTouchDetection\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"customCssClass\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"customHtmlId\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"customCssCode\";s:0:\"\";s:20:\"customUserAttributes\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"customLook\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"fragmentId\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"faName\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"faOptions\";a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}s:11:\"faCustomCss\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"urlExt\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"htmlTargetBlank\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"htmlTitle\";s:0:\"\";s:16:\"htmlDataRevealId\";s:0:\"\";s:18:\"htmlDataDropdownId\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"dropdownDirection\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"classOptions\";a:2:{i:0;s:0:\"\";i:1;s:5:\"small\";}s:10:\"buttonType\";s:0:\"\";}','M12.Foundation:Button',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',3,'/sites/m12/main/node53712f7134e24/col1/column/node53712f478e475/col4/column/node5372893ba9ac6/content','d2dc68b2b22275220cd75ae4765b0f9d','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','6d2f47be21cdaadf710652f5219cec46',NULL),('a69784eb-71a0-f9a5-e1b1-1e1c0b41910b','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/main/node5389f830a1599','6a928c26-9995-7b20-981a-54cd2b0f2fb2',1900,'a:4:{s:13:\"customTagName\";s:3:\"div\";s:4:\"text\";s:1031:\"<p>TYPO3 and Drupal target roughly the same market. But TYPO3 has a lot to catch up to be as equally recognisable and popular as Drupal. It needs a’la<em>TYPO3IA</em> to respond to <em>Acquia</em> strong marketing. It needs more advertising, it needs solutions like dedicated hosting, it needs companies who would offer support to enterprise customers. It needs PaaS and SaaS products based on TYPO3 which would popularise it (vs. e.g. <a href=\"http://www.drupalgardens.com/\">Drupal Gardens</a>). It needs talks and presence on conferences. And it has to be in English - some of us doesn’t speak German.</p><p>If my crystal orb is right, at least some of these we’re going to see happening in 2014 and following years. With new TYPO3 CMS 6.x (continuation of 4.x), completely new TYPO3 Neos - notabene both based on the same <a href=\"http://flow.typo3.org/\">TYPO3 Flow</a> v.2 framework - we’re in a good shape to change above numbers. And I’m ready to set my hand to the plough and help a little bit with that.</p>\";s:9:\"classHide\";b:0;s:13:\"classClearfix\";b:0;}','TYPO3.Neos.NodeTypes:Text',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',2,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/main','af3568fa18f43c5ff3bc1bd214258be1','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','af55dff3a021a46d7b34772bf1d97f4f',NULL),('a97d1873-483d-5043-efb6-1776e8303c1f','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/synopsis/node5389f40a9a15e','bd9090bf-3d1f-e141-a70d-741378cea109',100,'a:4:{s:13:\"customTagName\";s:3:\"div\";s:4:\"text\";s:792:\"<p>Year 2014 is going to be busy both in <a href=\"http://drupal.org/\">Drupal</a> and <a href=\"http://typo3.org/\">TYPO3 CMS</a> camps. TYPO3 has just released completely new flagship <a href=\"http://neos.typo3.org/\">TYPO3 Neos</a>, beautifully designed and written from the scratch, with content-first approach, focused on author and developer experience (if you haven’t try it yet, you must do!). From Drupal camp, on the horizon we have <a href=\"https://drupal.org/\">Drupal 8</a> (currently alpha) which promises to be revolutionary too. After a nearly 3-years-long affair with Drupal I’m coming back to TYPO3 world (the <em>why</em> is a topic for separate and rather a long post) - therefore it was interesting to look at current stats and trends regarding these two.<br/></p>\";s:9:\"classHide\";b:0;s:13:\"classClearfix\";b:0;}','TYPO3.Neos.NodeTypes:Text',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',2,'/sites/m12/blog/typo3-vs-drupal-stats/synopsis','f035ae49a72da8ae9aa4609541f33bb3','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','f9071da5d4ee94c9556b05ce1edb066d',NULL),('aae8fd3b-cd5f-b352-fdb8-65c16f4703e9','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/blog/vagrant-with-typo3-flow-neos/main','3f3b2031-41c8-0bc8-836f-7a660ce4cc23',200,'a:0:{}','TYPO3.Neos:ContentCollection',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'a:0:{}',2,'/sites/m12/blog/vagrant-with-typo3-flow-neos','4fa8f7be511dab2c07a79fd0db91e359','d751713988987e9331980363e24189ce','a:0:{}','b2baa4e37319618365cbe98b84c14247',NULL),('adedeb47-54fd-521b-fab4-139121c01a6c','live',NULL,'/sites/m12/main/node53712414795c7/col1/column/node5371247d99b66','c38625ec-07a3-1542-28c1-4210fa980f2e',100,'a:21:{s:13:\"customTagName\";s:6:\"header\";s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"<h1>About us</h1>\";s:9:\"classHide\";b:0;s:13:\"classClearfix\";b:0;s:10:\"classFloat\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"classTextAlign\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"classRadiusAndRounded\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"classShowByScreenSize\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"classHideByScreenSize\";s:0:\"\";s:25:\"classOrientationDetection\";s:0:\"\";s:19:\"classTouchDetection\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"customCssClass\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"customHtmlId\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"customCssCode\";s:0:\"\";s:20:\"customUserAttributes\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"customLook\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"fragmentId\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"mag